CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773753074
OL,3,CThe physical, psychological and social
OL,4,Cwounds suffered by children in Lebanon
OL,6,FLebanon's healthcare system is
OL,7,Fprecarious at best, after years of
OL,8,Feconomic decline, and barely able to
OL,9,Fcope in those fleeting moments when
OL,10,Fthere isn't a war. Now entire families
OL,11,Fneed treating and he fears this is
OL,12,Fonly the start of a brutal period in
OL,13,Fthe country's history.
OL,15,FAnd it is not just the physical
OL,16,Finjures that will haunt, war brings
OL,17,Fwith it social rupture from which
OL,18,Frecovery is only limited.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773753074
OL,3,CThe physical, psychological and social
OL,4,Cwounds suffered by children in Lebanon
OL,6,F"I have a child who's lost both
OL,7,Fparents and all three siblings. I have
OL,8,Fanother child who had shrapnel in her
OL,9,Fface and her eyes, whose mother was
OL,10,Fkilled when she was on her lap.
OL,12,F"All of my kids are being wounded with
OL,13,Ftheir families and so what you're
OL,14,Fwitnessing is a physical wound and an
OL,15,Femotional, psychological and social
OL,16,Fwound.
OL,18,F"It's also existential - these
OL,19,Fchildren believed that the safest
OL,20,Fplace was home, and that their parents
OL,21,Fwould never let anything bad happen.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773753074
OL,3,CThe physical, psychological and social
OL,4,Cwounds suffered by children in Lebanon
OL,6,F"And so their whole world view is
OL,7,Fshattered, and I saw that in Gaza over
OL,8,Fand over again, and we're seeing it
OL,9,Fagain in Lebanon."
OL,11,FHe has done this job now for three
OL,12,Fdecades.
OL,14,F"What is still morally shocking is the
OL,15,Ffact that the treatment of these
OL,16,Fchildren costs less than the missile
OL,17,Fthat injures them," he said. "And that
OL,18,Fis the kind of moral abyss that
OL,19,Fhumanity keeps falling into."
OL,21,FDoes he have any hope of change? No.
OL,26,@qD@RO]vD@AOU{D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/8
